			<description><![CDATA[<pre style="margin: 0px; word-wrap: break-word; white-space: pre-line; width: 99%; font: 100% sans-serif;">
Chief Technology Officer at PeerPong

About the Job

The Chief Technology Officer&#39;s role is to assure the successful execution of the company&#39;s business mission through development and deployment of PeerPong&#39;s semantic index and applications.

PeerPong is  a social/semantic search company building the largest index and community of expertise on the web. We&#39;ve raised seed capital from Partech, First Round Capital, and DCM.

Responsibilities:

The CTO will be instrumental in helping to scale PeerPong&#39;s cutting-edge NLP/semantic index and engine.  This person should have deep knowledge and experience in both NLP/Semantics/indexing, as well as in the deployment of enterprise-ready applications and platforms. He/she must also be able to evaluate and identify appropriate processes, methods and platforms for the delivery of PeerPong&#39;s products. 

Required Skills:

    * 7+ years experience leading and managing a team of engineers
    * Experience in NLP/Semantics and the enterprise application space
    * Strong aptitude for determining the optimal way to use cutting edge technology in our market place
    * Supervise recruitment, training, retention, and organization of all development staff in accordance with the company hiring process, personnel policies, and budget requirements
    * Build and manage a top caliber development team and oversee the development &amp; project management of PeerPong&#39;s index and applicatons
    * Deep technology understanding of Ruby, MongoDB, SOLR, MySQL, Python/Perl
    * We are looking for an enthusiastic, performance-driven self-starter and team player
    * Previous start-up experience is a strong plus
    * CS/EE/Engineering degree preferred

We are a fast-paced technology company developing a new paradigm in semantic and social search. At PeerPong, you will find smart, creative people who are passionate about taking on new challenges. 

    * This position is located at our headquarters in San Francisco
    * Competitive salary, equity
    * We provide full benefits: dental, vision, healthcare</pre>
